  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;div&gt;The proposed advertisement, by reason of its scale, appearance, location and method of illumination would result in an obstructive and intrusive form of development that would obstruct the pavement, reduce the amount of space available for use by pedestrians, block lines of sight creating blind spots and create distractions for highway users reducing the safety of the highway. As such the proposed development is contrary to policy D8 &#x27;Public Realm&#x27; of the London Plan (2021) as well as policy PP1 &#x27;Public Realm&#x27;, LP7 &#x27;Advertisements&#x27; and LP42 &#x27;Walking and Cycling&#x27; of the Hackney Local Plan.&lt;/div&gt;",
    "&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, &amp;quot;sans-serif&amp;quot;; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;&quot;&gt;The proposed advertisement,\r\nby reason of its scale, location and illumination, would result in an\r\nincongruous form of street clutter that would have an intrusive impact, to the\r\ndetriment of the character and appearance of the application site and\r\nsurrounding streetscape. The proposal is therefore contrary to D4 (Delivering good design) of the London Plan (2021); Policies LP1 (Design) and LP7 (Advertisement) of the adopted Hackney Local Plan (2020) and guidance under the NPPF.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
